13 SECTION 3. REAPPROPRIATION AUTHORITY FOR THE DEPARTMENT OF ENVIRONMEN-
14 TAL QUALITY (GENERAL) FUND. There is hereby reappropriated to the Department
15 of Environmental Quality any unexpended and unencumbered balances appropri-
16 ated to the Department of Environmental Quality in the Administration and
17 Support Services Program from the General Fund not to exceed $2,500,000 from
18 the Department of Environmental Quality (General) Fund, to be used for non-
19 recurring expenditures related to document management implementation for
20 the period July 1, 2025, through June 30, 2026. The Office of the State Con-
21 troller shall confirm the reappropriation amount, by fund, expense class,
22 and program, with the Legislative Services Office prior to processing the
23 reappropriation authorized herein.
24 SECTION 4. CASH TRANSFER FOR DRINKING AND WASTEWATER GRANTS. There
25 is hereby appropriated to the Department of Environmental Quality and the
26 Office of the State Controller shall transfer $10,000,000 from the General
27 Fund to the Water Pollution Control Fund on July 1, 2025, or as soon there-
28 after as practicable for the period July 1, 2025, through June 30, 2026, to be
29 used for drinking and wastewater grants.
30 SECTION 5. DRINKING AND WASTEWATER GRANTS. It is the intent of the Leg-
31 islature to provide up to $10,000,000 for up to five years to support con-
32 struction of drinking water and wastewater projects. The Department of En-
33 vironmental Quality will provide funding in the form of grants for construc-
34 tion of drinking water and wastewater projects using a tiered approach that
35 provides the highest level of grant funding to prioritize smaller systems
36 and other factors, including monthly user rates, median income, and readi-
37 ness to proceed. The Department may also use funds appropriated pursuant to
38 Section 1 of this act to fund eligible planning grant requests received con-
39 sistent with existing department processes. These moneys shall be adminis-

