4 vices Office no later than December 1, 2025. The report shall include iden-
5 tification of the grant recipients and grant amounts and the balance of any
6 appropriated funds not committed to recipients at the time of the report be-
7 ing submitted.
8 SECTION 6. CONDITIONS, LIMITATIONS, AND RESTRICTIONS. Appropriations
9 made pursuant to this act are subject to the conditions, limitations, and re-
10 strictions specified in this act.
11 SECTION 7. EXEMPTIONS FROM EXPENSE CLASS AND PROGRAM TRANSFER LIM-
12 ITATIONS. For fiscal year 2025, the Department of Environmental Quality
13 is hereby exempted from the provisions of Section 67-3511(2), Idaho Code,
14 allowing unlimited transfers between programs for indirect costs, for all
15 moneys appropriated to it for the period July 1, 2024, through June 30, 2025.
16 Legislative appropriations shall not be transferred from one fund to another
17 fund unless expressly approved by the Legislature.
18 SECTION 8. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
